$ Excel Object Model: OLEObject / MSForms / TextBox

{ functions.bas

 `functions.bas` is a → development/languages/VBA/language/module[VBA module] that crates a Forms-text box:

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/OLEObject/MSForms/textBox/functions.bas||

}
{ sheet1.bas

 `sheet1.bas` is the *sheet-module* that is needed to capture events of form controls placed on a given sheet.

  In order to stop a key from being prcocessed, `0` must be assigned to `keyCode` that is passed to the `_keyDown` event.

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/OLEObject/MSForms/textBox/sheet1.bas||

}
{ Result

  After being created, the text box looks like this:

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/OLEObject/MSForms/textBox/img/textBox.png||

}
{ create.wsf

  The workbook with this two sheets can be created with the → Microsoft/Office/VBScript-App-Creator[VB Script MS-Office App creator] ant the following script:

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/OLEObject/MSForms/textBox/create.wsf||

}
